1
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:12,300
Noble and I saw a pattern

2
00:00:12,433 --> 00:00:13,600
in the icepick killer,

3
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:15,200
it's not just gays.

4
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:17,100
We're looking
for a serial killer.

5
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:19,333
They said this isn't
just any hate crime.

6
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:21,267
- There's a pattern.
- What pattern? What? Bingo?

7
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:22,267
Where's my umbrella?

8
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,500
Girl, someone stole that.

9
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:24,700
- It's too pretty.
- What?

10
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:26,500
Miss, your change is not enough.

11
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:27,367
Let me see.

12
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:28,833
Miss, you're so kind.

13
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:30,967
Bless your heart.

14
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:33,367
Chief is right. This is outside
our jurisdiction.

15
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:34,200
What's your plan?

16
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:36,133
I need to talk
to the contractors.

17
00:00:36,267 --> 00:00:37,333
I need to know

18
00:00:37,467 --> 00:00:40,167
if Mayor Glen is really involved
in this ghost project.

19
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:42,100
You want me to take down
that reporter!

20
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:44,200
Where is the engineer
I asked you to find?

21
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:46,233
Boss, I know where he's hiding.

22
00:00:46,367 --> 00:00:47,033
Go get him.

23
00:00:47,167 --> 00:00:48,200
Oh my, Ma'am, I'm sorry.

24
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:49,700
I don't know where boss is.

25
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:50,800
What is this about?

26
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:52,733
- What do you think?
- Delaying tactic.

27
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:53,933
I have a feeling
they've been warned.

28
00:00:54,067 --> 00:00:55,800
Sir, that's what
I'm calling you about.

29
00:00:55,933 --> 00:00:57,267
My vision has cleared up.

30
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,400
<i>What I was saying
about your rainbow design,</i>

31
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:00,933
<i>- that's an umbrella!
- There!</i>

32
00:01:01,067 --> 00:01:02,100
The target is there.

33
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:05,267
I'm sure the killer is around.

34
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:06,867
Oh! Who are you?

35
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,667
Help!

36
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:10,833
Stop it! Raise your hand!

37
00:01:10,967 --> 00:01:11,967
Stop!

38
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:13,500
Chase him!

39
00:01:15,633 --> 00:01:17,167
Help!

40
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:18,300
Hold on! Hold on!

41
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:20,333
Apply pressure!

42
00:01:20,467 --> 00:01:22,967
Requesting emergency
medical response.

43
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:26,367
Male victim,
stabbed at the side.

44
00:02:03,933 --> 00:02:07,800
Lieutenant Samson,
here's what you're asking for.

45
00:02:07,933 --> 00:02:09,667
Thank you, Sergeant Enriquez.

46
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:13,467
You know, a desk job
really suits you.

47
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:14,700
All right.

48
00:02:14,867 --> 00:02:17,133
Oh, wait a minute,
I have something else to order.

49
00:02:17,267 --> 00:02:18,500
What's that?

50
00:02:18,633 --> 00:02:19,933
Coffee, would you like?

51
00:02:20,067 --> 00:02:21,233
No.

52
00:02:21,367 --> 00:02:22,167
- I'm okay.
- That's okay.

53
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:23,567
That's okay, right?

54
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:25,067
What? Do you want it?

55
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:26,667
Well, my duty is over.

56
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,033
I'm on my way home.

57
00:02:28,167 --> 00:02:30,067
I'll go ahead.

58
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:31,767
Enriquez...

59
00:02:33,533 --> 00:02:35,100
Can we talk?

60
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:37,000
Oh, let's have a snack first.

61
00:02:37,133 --> 00:02:40,000
Oh, Conde, it's a good thing
you're here.

62
00:02:40,133 --> 00:02:42,200
Do you want us to have dinner?

63
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:43,833
Bobby, you're leaving, right?

64
00:02:43,967 --> 00:02:46,133
All right.

65
00:02:46,267 --> 00:02:48,133
Okay, you can go.

66
00:02:51,033 --> 00:02:53,167
Okay, Sir.

67
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:55,533
Perfect, I'm hungry too.

68
00:02:55,667 --> 00:02:56,700
Where do you want
to have dinner?

69
00:02:56,833 --> 00:03:00,067
Oh, no, Lieutenant Samson.

70
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,367
It's okay, I'm still full.

71
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:10,967
Samson, stop bothering Conde.

72
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:15,200
Paloma, Samson,

73
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:16,933
Chief is calling us.

74
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:27,033
Don't kill me!

75
00:03:27,167 --> 00:03:29,567
Don't! Don't!

76
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,733
Boss! Boss!

77
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:33,400
Boss, have mercy, Boss!

78
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:36,467
Engineer Marasigan,
long time no see.

79
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:37,467
Boss...

80
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:39,433
I know I owe you a lot,

81
00:03:39,567 --> 00:03:42,233
but maybe you can give me at
least one more chance, Boss.

82
00:03:42,367 --> 00:03:43,633
Boss...

83
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:44,767
Have mercy.

84
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,733
Goodbye, Engineer Marasigan.

85
00:03:46,867 --> 00:03:48,100
- See you in hell.
- Don't, Boss.

86
00:03:48,233 --> 00:03:49,767
Don't, Boss! Have mercy!

87
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:51,700
I have a family, Boss!

88
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:53,700
Don't worry.

89
00:03:53,833 --> 00:03:55,767
I can kill them next.

90
00:03:55,933 --> 00:03:58,033
Or do you want them to go first?

91
00:03:58,167 --> 00:03:59,167
That's fine.

92
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:00,300
You choose.

93
00:04:00,433 --> 00:04:03,033
Don't involve them, Boss!

94
00:04:03,167 --> 00:04:04,400
I'll do anything, anything!

95
00:04:04,533 --> 00:04:05,867
Whatever you want, Boss!

96
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:06,967
Just tell me, Boss!

97
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:08,833
Really? You'll do anything?

98
00:04:08,967 --> 00:04:10,667
Yes, Boss,
I'll do anything, Boss!

99
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,767
I don't believe it.

100
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:12,933
Oh, no, Boss!

101
00:04:13,067 --> 00:04:14,367
Have mercy, Boss!

102
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:16,000
Oh, no!

103
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:17,133
No, Boss!

104
00:04:17,267 --> 00:04:19,300
Have mercy on me,
don't kill me, Boss!

105
00:04:21,567 --> 00:04:24,800
Okay, okay, okay...

106
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:30,167
I'll give you another chance.

107
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:32,367
Thank you very much, Boss.

108
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:36,467
I'll make it up to you.
I'll do anything.

109
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:39,033
Just tell me, Boss.

110
00:04:39,167 --> 00:04:42,133
Are you ready to do anything
for your family?

111
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:43,267
Yes, Boss.

112
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:45,467
I'll do it, Boss, I'll do it.

113
00:04:56,767 --> 00:04:59,100
Conde, how's the victim?

114
00:04:59,233 --> 00:05:00,733
I've already given instructions,
Chief,

115
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:02,300
To keep a tight guard on him

116
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:03,833
because the killer
might come back.

117
00:05:03,967 --> 00:05:08,000
Our victim, Patricia,
has previous records, Sir.

118
00:05:08,133 --> 00:05:10,300
He has a previous Estafa case.

119
00:05:10,433 --> 00:05:12,067
He's also a scammer, Sir.

120
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:14,500
Even though he's a scammer,

121
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:18,367
that killer still has no right
to end his life.

122
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:21,367
Good job, Conde, Dizon.

123
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:26,000
I can feel this killer
is about to be caught.

124
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:27,233
Garcia...

125
00:05:27,367 --> 00:05:29,167
What's the update on your case?

126
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:34,233
Sir, we're following a new lead.

127
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,200
We have a lot of cases now.

128
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:39,167
With Mateo Ramos,

129
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:40,867
we don't have an update yet.

130
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,500
Noble, you might think

131
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:44,067
I don't know what you're doing.

132
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:46,367
Maybe you're getting
influenced by Enriquez.

133
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,000
This is the last one.

134
00:05:48,133 --> 00:05:51,467
Let's not interfere
if it's not our job.

135
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,900
We might even end up at odds
with the mayor.

136
00:05:54,033 --> 00:05:55,700
Yes, Sir.

137
00:05:55,833 --> 00:06:00,300
Obviously, we're all busy.

138
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:02,900
And I'm asking all of you
to step up...

139
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:05,100
and close the cases.

140
00:06:05,233 --> 00:06:06,967
I want better results,

141
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:09,033
especially the one you're
handling, Garcia.

142
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,800
We need to find out

143
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:12,467
who the mastermind is.

144
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,500
Yes, Sir.

145
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:16,900
Okay, you're dismissed.

146
00:06:17,033 --> 00:06:19,000
Thank you, Sir.

147
00:06:55,167 --> 00:06:57,767
<i> And let me remind you.</i>

148
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:59,000
<i>You're on a desk job assignment,</i>

149
00:06:59,133 --> 00:07:01,933
<i> and give everything to Conde.</i>

150
00:07:07,033 --> 00:07:08,300
<i>Noble, where's the one
we're chasing?</i>

151
00:07:08,433 --> 00:07:09,667
<i> Sir, he got away.</i>

152
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,133
<i> What? How did he get away?</i>

153
00:07:11,267 --> 00:07:12,567
<i> Ma'am Bobby bumped into him.</i>

154
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:16,467
<i>Lieutenant Samson, this is the
one you're looking for.</i>

155
00:07:16,633 --> 00:07:18,367
<i> Thank you, Sergeant Enriquez.</i>

156
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:21,067
<i>You know, you're really
good at desk work.</i>

157
00:07:29,167 --> 00:07:33,067
<i>I don't want to blame you
for the suspect getting away,</i>

158
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:35,033
<i> but look at Noble.</i>

159
00:07:35,167 --> 00:07:36,600
<i>Oh, what if you were the one
who got hurt?</i>

160
00:07:36,733 --> 00:07:39,133
<i>What? You caught up with him,
but then fought back.</i>

161
00:07:39,267 --> 00:07:40,800
<i> I can fight for myself.</i>

162
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:43,800
<i>I'm just protecting you
from yourself.</i>

163
00:07:55,333 --> 00:07:57,233
Grandchild...

164
00:08:01,533 --> 00:08:05,400
Oh, why are you crying?

165
00:08:06,867 --> 00:08:08,000
I'm just tired.

166
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:09,900
Tired?

167
00:08:10,033 --> 00:08:12,100
Oh my, grandchild.

168
00:08:12,233 --> 00:08:17,733
When you're tired,
you should rest.

169
00:08:17,867 --> 00:08:19,833
Ah, yes, by the way,

170
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:23,533
you know I saved some
of your favorite dish,

171
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:26,933
the adobong puti.

172
00:08:27,067 --> 00:08:29,067
Oh, wait a minute.

173
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,400
I'll heat it up.

174
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:31,633
I'll get it ready.

175
00:08:31,767 --> 00:08:33,733
We'll both eat.

176
00:08:33,867 --> 00:08:35,667
Just stay there.

177
00:08:47,567 --> 00:08:49,800
You can do this, Bobby.

178
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:52,267
Just don't give up.

179
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:03,000
How did they know
my next target was?

180
00:09:03,133 --> 00:09:05,533
How?

181
00:09:05,667 --> 00:09:08,333
This can't be...

182
00:09:08,467 --> 00:09:11,033
This can't be!

183
00:09:16,567 --> 00:09:19,267
I need to be more
careful next time.

184
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,500
I'll never fail again!

185
00:09:21,633 --> 00:09:23,633
No more! No more! No more!

186
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:31,333
Don't...

187
00:09:31,467 --> 00:09:32,900
Don't!

188
00:09:47,633 --> 00:09:49,233
Hello? Hello?

189
00:09:49,367 --> 00:09:50,400
Hello, Sir Tonyo?

190
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,233
Sir!

191
00:09:54,367 --> 00:09:56,133
I know what the killer
looks like!

192
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:12,200
Mother, good morning.

193
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,833
What do you need?

194
00:10:20,367 --> 00:10:24,033
Are you Mrs. Vergel?

195
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:27,100
Yes, that's me.

196
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:28,933
Why?

197
00:10:29,067 --> 00:10:33,000
I just wanted to talk to you
about Matmat.

198
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,567
You should leave.

199
00:10:34,733 --> 00:10:37,500
My son hasn't been home
for a while.

200
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:46,600
Mother, I just wanted
to ask you something.

201
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:49,767
I just wanted to know

202
00:10:49,900 --> 00:10:53,367
if Matmat was maltreatred
when he was a child.

203
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:01,800
Oh, Jake!

204
00:11:01,933 --> 00:11:03,700
How did it go with Major?

205
00:11:03,833 --> 00:11:05,533
Did you get scolded?

206
00:11:05,667 --> 00:11:07,300
No, not really.

207
00:11:07,433 --> 00:11:10,067
Just asking for an update
on the ongoing cases.

208
00:11:10,233 --> 00:11:12,933
That's good,
I thought you got scolded.

209
00:11:13,067 --> 00:11:14,467
No.

210
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:17,500
- Noble.
- Oh, Sir?

211
00:11:17,633 --> 00:11:18,767
What's that, Sir?

212
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:20,300
Look.

213
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:25,467
I dug up the financial report

214
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,167
of the construction company
that is in charge

215
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:30,367
of the ghost project
you are talking about.

216
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:33,900
And I also found out that
they just hired a subcontractor.

217
00:11:34,033 --> 00:11:37,200
Sir, how did you know that
we were investigating someone?

218
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:38,933
That's not important anymore.

219
00:11:39,067 --> 00:11:42,000
What's important is that
we catch their accomplice,

220
00:11:42,167 --> 00:11:43,467
unless you don't want my help.

221
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:44,800
Oh, no, Sir.

222
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:45,933
This is a big help.

223
00:11:46,067 --> 00:11:47,367
Thank you very much.

224
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:48,667
I think the subcon is the one
who can answer

225
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,300
where the budget went.

226
00:11:50,433 --> 00:11:51,833
Let's go, I'll come with you.

227
00:11:51,967 --> 00:11:53,200
You'll come with us, Sir?

228
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:56,567
Yes, so that Chief
won't scold you anymore.

229
00:11:58,567 --> 00:12:00,267
Let's go.

230
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,233
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

231
00:12:06,167 --> 00:12:09,667
At first, I didn't know

232
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:13,600
why my husband was so angry

233
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:16,267
with our only child.

234
00:12:16,433 --> 00:12:19,600
He always hurt Matmat.

235
00:12:19,733 --> 00:12:22,833
There was nothing I could do
because...

236
00:12:22,967 --> 00:12:24,933
if I stopped him,

237
00:12:25,067 --> 00:12:27,767
he would beat me up.

238
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:31,833
He always accuses me
of having another man,

239
00:12:31,967 --> 00:12:35,233
that Matmat is not his son.

240
00:12:35,367 --> 00:12:37,500
He's a con artist.

241
00:12:37,633 --> 00:12:41,067
He fooled a lot of people
for money,

242
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:46,333
but not once did he have
a police record...

243
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:48,633
because he's good
at getting away with it.

244
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:55,600
You and your husband
haven't reconciled?

245
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:58,567
No, not anymore.

246
00:12:58,700 --> 00:13:02,033
Ever since I found out
he was cheating on me.

247
00:13:02,167 --> 00:13:03,867
Cheating?

248
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,033
Does that mean he has another
woman?

249
00:13:06,167 --> 00:13:10,033
No! He has another man.

250
00:13:10,167 --> 00:13:12,733
That animal is a closet gay.

251
00:13:12,867 --> 00:13:13,900
Oh...

252
00:13:17,333 --> 00:13:19,833
I want to help you, Mother.

253
00:13:19,967 --> 00:13:22,633
Do you know
where to find Matmat?

254
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:25,300
I don't know either.

255
00:13:25,433 --> 00:13:27,833
He hasn't contacted me...

256
00:13:27,967 --> 00:13:31,033
or even shown himself to me
for a long time.

257
00:13:34,133 --> 00:13:38,400
Do you have a photo
of Matmat there?

258
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:41,200
I do, but it's old.

259
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:42,233
It's okay.

260
00:13:42,367 --> 00:13:44,067
I just want to see it.

261
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,333
Wait a minute, okay?
I'll get it.

262
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:46,967
Okay.

263
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,433
This is my son.

264
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:10,767
This is Mateo Ramos.

265
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:11,900
Yes.

266
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:16,000
Matmat's real name
is Mateo Ramos.

267
00:14:27,467 --> 00:14:29,167
- Alma! What? What's the news?
- Sir...

268
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:31,033
Sir Tonyo, I've seen the killer.

269
00:14:31,167 --> 00:14:33,567
Oh my, Sir, I saw
what he looks like.

270
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:34,800
That's good.

271
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:37,167
I'm going to take you
to our sketch artist

272
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:39,300
so you can describe
the killer's face to him.

273
00:14:39,433 --> 00:14:41,633
Oh, okay, Sir. I really want
this to be over.

274
00:14:41,767 --> 00:14:45,233
But I want you to know...

275
00:14:45,367 --> 00:14:47,500
that I haven't told my boss yet,

276
00:14:47,633 --> 00:14:50,500
that the leads I'm following
came from you.

277
00:14:50,633 --> 00:14:52,533
Why?

278
00:14:52,667 --> 00:14:54,100
Because they won't believe

279
00:14:54,233 --> 00:14:56,600
if you say
it's from a fortune teller?

280
00:14:56,733 --> 00:14:59,000
Alma, I know you've helped
a lot with this case.

281
00:14:59,133 --> 00:14:59,833
If it weren't for you,

282
00:14:59,967 --> 00:15:04,233
Patricia might have died.

283
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:07,100
I just don't know
how he'd react

284
00:15:07,233 --> 00:15:11,300
if I tell him
that you were my source.

285
00:15:11,433 --> 00:15:12,833
It's okay, Sir Tonyo.

286
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:15,633
I don't want people to know

287
00:15:15,767 --> 00:15:17,500
that I have this kind
of thing either.

288
00:15:17,633 --> 00:15:20,233
It's not fun when a dead person
visits you.

289
00:15:20,367 --> 00:15:21,400
Oh, my Lord.

290
00:15:21,533 --> 00:15:23,433
You know, after this,
I'll really be good.

291
00:15:23,567 --> 00:15:26,067
I'll stop this racket and,
that's it!

292
00:15:27,067 --> 00:15:27,933
No more.

293
00:15:28,067 --> 00:15:30,367
That's good,
so we can get this over with.

294
00:15:30,733 --> 00:15:31,833
What? Let's go?

295
00:15:31,967 --> 00:15:33,500
Okay.

296
00:15:35,533 --> 00:15:37,133
Sir, Sir...

297
00:15:37,267 --> 00:15:39,567
I already know
who the killer is.

298
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:41,700
It's Mateo Ramos.

299
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:54,733
Sir, it's good that you got this
intel about the subcon.

300
00:15:55,667 --> 00:15:57,300
Just do proper search, Noble.

301
00:15:57,433 --> 00:15:59,067
The one we're going to talk
to today

302
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:03,567
is the owner of the subcon
construction company.

303
00:16:03,967 --> 00:16:07,367
I'm sure we can get a lot
of information from here.

304
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:08,533
Hey!

305
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:11,167
Stop!

306
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:17,833
It looks like him!

307
00:16:17,967 --> 00:16:19,533
It looks like the one I saw!

308
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:22,600
But...

309
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:25,267
No, he's bald!

310
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:27,167
Yes, without hair.

311
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:29,033
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

312
00:16:29,167 --> 00:16:31,300
It looks like...

313
00:16:31,433 --> 00:16:32,967
- Bald?
- Yes.

314
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:34,633
As in, no more hair.

315
00:16:34,767 --> 00:16:36,633
- Alma!
- Is it him?

316
00:16:36,767 --> 00:16:38,733
Are you sure
that's what you saw?

317
00:16:38,867 --> 00:16:40,567
Sir, it's the one I saw!

318
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:42,900
Yes! Yes!

319
00:16:43,067 --> 00:16:44,933
- Are you sure?
- Yes!

320
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:46,333
Yes!

321
00:16:46,467 --> 00:16:48,000
Oh, I'm sure, Sir!

322
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:49,200
He's the one I saw!

323
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:50,567
Wait, how did that happen?

324
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:52,867
- Are you sure?
- Yes!

325
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:56,800
Because Mateo Ramos
has no record of murder.

326
00:16:56,933 --> 00:16:58,567
He was in prison for robbery.

327
00:16:58,700 --> 00:17:00,967
He hasn't been caught
for murder yet, Sir.

328
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:04,533
But we have a cold case here
where he is the suspect

329
00:17:04,667 --> 00:17:06,900
I talked to Mateo Ramos' mother,

330
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:09,700
and she said that
when Mateo was little,

331
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:11,267
his father maltreated him.

332
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:16,767
And his father is a cheater,
a scammer, a swindler.

333
00:17:16,933 --> 00:17:19,300
I have a profile
of the icepick killer, Sir.

334
00:17:19,433 --> 00:17:21,233
He really is targeting someone.

335
00:17:21,367 --> 00:17:22,700
It's all the same.

336
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,700
Cheater, abusive parent,

337
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,300
scammer, swindler,

338
00:17:26,433 --> 00:17:27,500
and it's the same thing.

339
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:30,900
But why are his victims gay?

340
00:17:31,033 --> 00:17:34,733
Because the father who hurt him
is a closet gay.

341
00:17:34,867 --> 00:17:37,367
That's probably why his victims
are gay too.

342
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:42,467
Have you told Chief
all this information yet?

343
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:45,200
Not yet, Sir.

344
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:46,800
Conde.

345
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:53,200
What are you and Enriquez
talking about?

346
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:57,067
Sir, Enriquez has something
to tell you.

347
00:18:02,667 --> 00:18:04,500
- Boss...
- And you even keep on running.

348
00:18:04,633 --> 00:18:05,567
Boss...

349
00:18:05,700 --> 00:18:08,333
You want to give us a hard time.

350
00:18:08,467 --> 00:18:10,267
Do you think you can escape us?

351
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:13,400
Boss, boss, I have a lot
of money, I have a lot!

352
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:15,067
How much do you need?

353
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,800
I'll make sure
that everything you say,

354
00:18:16,933 --> 00:18:18,733
I'll add to our case
against you.

355
00:18:18,867 --> 00:18:20,733
Remember, not all police
officers

356
00:18:20,867 --> 00:18:22,500
can be bought with your money.

357
00:18:22,667 --> 00:18:24,333
Boss...

358
00:18:24,467 --> 00:18:25,667
Give me a price.

359
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,933
- Oh, I'll give it to you.
- Stop it!

360
00:18:28,067 --> 00:18:29,833
I can change your life.

361
00:18:29,967 --> 00:18:32,133
- Oh...
- Sir.

362
00:18:32,267 --> 00:18:33,433
These are bank documents.

363
00:18:33,567 --> 00:18:36,500
This is solid evidence.

364
00:18:36,633 --> 00:18:37,800
Go ahead, Noble.

365
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:41,567
I'm sure you'll find more
evidence in his office.

366
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:43,167
Okay, Sir.

367
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,700
Get it all.

368
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,667
What's that again, Robles?

369
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:03,667
Is it about the ghost project?

370
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:05,033
Didn't I warn you already?

371
00:19:05,167 --> 00:19:06,067
Especially you, Noble?

372
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:09,833
Chief, maybe you could
listen to us first?

373
00:19:09,967 --> 00:19:13,667
Sir, we found out that the
project was just subcontracted.

374
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,067
We visited the engineer.

375
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,000
We caught him trying to escape.

376
00:19:17,133 --> 00:19:19,333
Sir, here are the signed
subcontractor,

377
00:19:19,467 --> 00:19:21,300
agreements and
liquidation papers.

378
00:19:21,433 --> 00:19:23,433
Here are the bank notes

379
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:27,000
with millions of transactions
in his account.

380
00:19:27,133 --> 00:19:29,167
Based on everything we have
here, Chief.

381
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:30,767
It looks like he cheated
the Mayor too.

382
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:35,167
Be thankful that it gave
a positive result...

383
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:37,467
because if not,

384
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:38,433
you'll be in trouble.

385
00:19:38,567 --> 00:19:40,000
Go ahead!

386
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,400
Okay, Sir.

387
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:49,833
Look at those documents.

388
00:19:49,967 --> 00:19:52,267
Good news!

389
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:54,433
Because Enriquez has discovered

390
00:19:54,567 --> 00:19:57,000
the serial killer we've been
looking for so long,

391
00:19:57,133 --> 00:19:59,467
and it's none other than
Mateo Ramos.

392
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:02,533
That means the one
who let Mando escape

393
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:04,867
had nothing to do with it.

394
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:09,700
Mateo just happened to escape
and kill two people.

395
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:15,400
So study that carefully.

396
00:20:15,533 --> 00:20:16,900
Yes, Sir!

397
00:20:29,467 --> 00:20:31,700
Enriquez is good, right?

398
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:35,067
Of course, I trained her.

399
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:37,233
She's really good.

400
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:41,367
Hurry up!

401
00:20:58,100 --> 00:20:59,967
Hello, Boss?

402
00:21:00,100 --> 00:21:03,367
Our guy inside, Regan, called.

403
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:06,633
The engineer you planted
in Station 12,

404
00:21:06,767 --> 00:21:08,100
they took the bait.

405
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:12,000
You're no longer tied
to ghost projects.

406
00:21:12,133 --> 00:21:13,700
Okay, Boss.

407
00:21:15,867 --> 00:21:18,633
Major Flores and I
just finished talking.

408
00:21:18,933 --> 00:21:20,567
Recently, I was made aware

409
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:22,367
that a project I signed

410
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:25,867
when I was still a councilor
that I thought was finished.

411
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:26,900
It turned out that the funds

412
00:21:27,033 --> 00:21:29,100
that were supposed to be
for that were stolen.

413
00:21:29,233 --> 00:21:31,967
The taxes that we all worked
hard for were stolen,

414
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:33,733
but it was my fault.

415
00:21:33,867 --> 00:21:36,000
Because I failed
to monitor the project,

416
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:37,867
but it will never happen again.

417
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:40,533
Because I will
personally monitor

418
00:21:40,667 --> 00:21:45,900
the approved public works
of Calabari.

419
00:21:46,633 --> 00:21:48,667
And in other news,

420
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:50,833
our police have discovered

421
00:21:50,967 --> 00:21:52,133
that one of the inmates

422
00:21:52,267 --> 00:21:53,967
who escaped from the Calabari
State Prison

423
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,900
is a serial killer.

424
00:21:56,033 --> 00:21:58,733
And to speed up
the search for him,

425
00:21:58,867 --> 00:22:03,100
we are ready to offer a reward,
a big reward for anyone

426
00:22:03,233 --> 00:22:06,700
<i>who can give a tip
on where he is hiding.</i>

427
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:16,000
One million for anyone
who can point out

428
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:18,367
where this Mateo Ramos
is hiding.

429
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:20,667
One identifying mark
is that he has a birthmark

430
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,000
on his right hand.

431
00:22:32,367 --> 00:22:33,933
Help us.

432
00:22:34,067 --> 00:22:35,900
Let's help each other.

433
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,867
Grandma, you left the rice
on the stove.

434
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:58,967
It's burnt already.

435
00:22:59,100 --> 00:23:01,700
And you left the water running.

436
00:23:01,833 --> 00:23:03,167
Grandmother, why are you
wearing this?

437
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:04,300
And you're wearing it wrong.

438
00:23:04,433 --> 00:23:06,133
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

439
00:23:06,267 --> 00:23:07,267
What are you doing?

440
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:09,167
That woman won't come with us.

441
00:23:09,300 --> 00:23:11,167
- Mom.
- No, Glen.

442
00:23:11,300 --> 00:23:12,867
Isn't it enough that
you've been showered

443
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,500
with my family's wealth?

444
00:23:14,633 --> 00:23:16,833
- What tip did you get?
- From Barangay Amador.

445
00:23:16,967 --> 00:23:19,633
They said they noticed a tenant
who always wears a mask.

446
00:23:19,767 --> 00:23:20,933
They said they saw a man

447
00:23:21,067 --> 00:23:22,233
with a birthmark
on his right hand.

448
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,500
Is anyone there?

449
00:23:23,633 --> 00:23:28,400
Oh, Sir, they're just
conducting a survey.

450
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:29,700
Mateo Ramos...

451
00:23:29,833 --> 00:23:31,767
- Stop!
- Tonyo!

452
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:34,400
Sir Tonyo has a new partner?

453
00:23:34,533 --> 00:23:35,833
She thinks she's so beautiful.

454
00:23:35,967 --> 00:23:38,433
Oh, Bobby, she's the troublesome
policewoman

455
00:23:38,567 --> 00:23:39,667
you're talking about!

456
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:42,267
You're really insulting her,
right?

457
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:44,100
Your mother is blue!
